description.p:
FIG. 1 is a side schematic view showing an implant in place with a heart wall and coronary vessel shown in cross-section;


FIG. 2 is an enlarged cross-sectional view of a vessel portion of the implant of FIG. 1 placed in a coronary vessel at the time of placement;


FIG. 3 is the view of FIG. 1 following an initial period of time for a tissue response to initiate;


FIG. 4 is the view of FIG. 3 following an additional period of time for the tissue response to fully develop to create a flap only partially covering the open end of the vessel portion during diastole to partially obstruct retrograde flow from the vessel into the heart; and


FIG. 5 is the view of FIG. 4 showing the flexible flap fully open in response to blood flow during systole to permit unobstructed flow from the conduit into the vessel.
